            {
                "s2_paper_id": "9cde322be9aafad1fad77394387bba31062c98ad",
                "title": "Bimahonian distributions",
                "year": 2007,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 33,
                "reference_count": 36,
                "abstract": "Motivated by permutation statistics, we define, for any complex reflection group W, a family of bivariate generating functions W\u03c3(t, q). They are defined either in terms of Hilbert series for W\u2010invariant polynomials when W acts diagonally on two sets of variables or, equivalently, as sums involving the fake degrees of irreducible representations for W. It is shown that W\u03c3(t, q) satisfies a \u2018bicyclic sieving phenomenon\u2019 which combinatorially interprets its values when t and q are certain roots of unity.",
                "authors": [
                    {
